Metabolic equivalent of task. Metabolic equivalent of task (MET) refers to the energy expenditure required to carry out a specifc activity, and 1 MET is the rate of energy expenditure while sitting at rest. This generally corresponds to an oxygen uptake of 3.5 milliliters per kilogram of body weight per minute. Physical activities frequently are classifed by their intensity using the MET value as a reference.

Constant Power is a great program for exercisers to maintain a constant intensity through out the workout. The machine automatically adjusts any time you increase or decrease your cadence.
Please keep your cadence at your target RPM. The fitness device will automatically adjust your level of speed or incline based on variations in your cadence.
Note: treadmills do not support Constant Power feature
For beginners, start off at a power of 150W and at an RPM of 60. If you then feel comfortable, gradually increase the target power.
Use the cadence and power graphs to track your performance and ensure that you are exercising at a precise level.
Interval training is a type of training that involves a series of low to high intensity workouts interspersed with rest or relief periods.
After conneciton to your fitness device, select the time values to alter the duration of the intensity and rest periods. By default the intensity and rest periods are the same duration as each other.
As the default number of cycles is 10, altering the interval times will change the total workout time.

Manually adjust the incline, speed, resistance level or cadence of the interval periods by selecting the values. On treadmills, use the console to adjust the speed and incline during your interval training.
Programs allow you to pick from our own existing workout programmes.

These programmes offer various different combinations of intensities, inclines and interval cycles. You can exercise under different intensities without manually changing the parameters during your workout.
Select your preferred programme to start your workout.
